					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-685830#post-1836636</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-685830/it-always-has-been-it-always-has-not-been#post-1836636</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 20 Aug 2013 14:32:32 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Djoric</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>388108</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Ayup.</p> <p>When this universe's iteration of 1449 died, it caused a restructuring event. This was the best way I could justify the existence of the SPC because, like you said, there's no way they would occur naturally, and the entire point of the exercise was to see if I could treat the Center as a serious thing while retaining its batshit nonsense core.</p> <p>So I broke reality and made the world go insane.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-685830#post-1836601</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-685830/it-always-has-been-it-always-has-not-been#post-1836601</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 20 Aug 2013 13:15:28 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>HammerMaiden</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1552358</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This tickles my conjecture bone, and trying to trace the connections, allusions, and various other references sent me for a tizzy when I first read the words &quot;the First Punch&quot;. Seriously, if I had been drinking coffee, that would have been grounds for a spit-take.</p> <p>Well done. You've just made one of the oldest in-jokes ever into the most hilariously serious tale I've read in a looooong time. Very Prachett/Adams of you.</p> <p>+1 (but you already knew that).</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-685830#post-1836600</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-685830/it-always-has-been-it-always-has-not-been#post-1836600</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 20 Aug 2013 13:14:02 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Rioghail</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1302192</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The baseline alternate Dreamtime-accessible universe's &quot;totem creature&quot; is also a shark. It's a <em>whale shark</em>. This doesn't look to me like a post-restructuring event, just a universe which is a bit wackier than the baseline (AKA the universe in which the SPC can exist).</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-685830#post-1836580</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-685830/it-always-has-been-it-always-has-not-been#post-1836580</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 20 Aug 2013 12:25:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Drewbear</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>301632</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Okay, so this is an alternate Dreamtime-accessible universe where their &quot;totem creature&quot; isn't a whale, like baseline Foundation-verse, but a shark. Only it might be a post-restructing event baseline Foundation-verse. Interesting. And SPC actually doesn't bother me here, because you actually treated them relatively seriously, rather than as a one-note joke.</p> <p>Actually, the more I think about it, the more I think that the universe of this Tale is a post-restructuring-event 'verse, since the antics of the SPC are just <em>too</em> over the top. I can't see that particular culture/society actually occuring &quot;naturally&quot;.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
